<div class="Markdown_markdownContainer__UyYrv">
<p>Keeping pace with these emerging e-commerce trends will be imperative for brands looking to stay competitive and meet evolving consumer preferences in international markets.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h1>The E-commerce Imperative for Modern Businesses</h1>
<p>Online commerce is no longer an option but a necessity for businesses to achieve scale, enter new markets, and deliver convenience to digitally-connected consumers worldwide. Developing an international e-commerce strategy with Canada as a starting point allows optimizing operations before expanding globally. By leveraging turnkey solutions like Shopify Plus and capitalizing on emerging trends, businesses can drive sustainable cross-border growth amidst the booming e-commerce landscape. The time is now for forward-thinking brands to seize international opportunities and establish their digital footprint across geographies.</p>
<p>With projected revenues of over $5.7 trillion in 2022, global e-commerce represents the future of business growth. Canada’s flourishing digital commerce landscape, high mobile adoption and Shopify’s dominance make it an optimal launchpad for e-commerce expansion. By localizing strategies and leveraging analytics, businesses can streamline cross-border operations before accessing high-potential markets like the US, China, UK and India. The world of borderless e-commerce abounds with possibilities for brands seeking new customers and revenues globally.</p>
